  "response": "Okay, let's craft a sample daily schedule. To do this effectively, I need a little more information from you. Tell me about:\n\n**1. Your Goals & Priorities:**\n\n*   **What are your main goals?** (e.g., academic success, career advancement, improved fitness, creative pursuits, better work-life balance, relaxation, personal growth)\n*   **What is most important to you right now?**\n\n**2. Your Current Situation:**\n\n*   **What is your age range?** (e.g., student, young professional, parent, retiree) This helps understand your stage of life.\n*   **Do you work or go to school?** If so, what are your typical hours?\n*   **Do you have any regular commitments?** (e.g., family obligations, appointments, volunteer work)\n*   **What time do you usually wake up and go to bed?** (Roughly is fine)\n*   **What is your energy level like throughout the day?** Are you a morning person, a night owl, or somewhere in between?\n\n**3. Your Lifestyle & Preferences:**\n\n*   **Do you prefer structured routines or more flexibility?**\n*   **What activities do you enjoy and want to make time for?** (e.g., exercise, hobbies, socializing, reading, spending time in nature)\n*   **Are there any activities you want to eliminate or reduce?** (e.g., excessive screen time, procrastination)\n*   **Do you have any physical or mental health conditions that might affect your schedule?**\n\nIn the meantime, here is a sample schedule:\n\n**Sample Daily Schedule (Adaptable Template)**\n\nThis is a very generic template.  It's meant to be adjusted significantly based on your specific information!\n\n*   **6:00 - 7:00 AM:** Wake up, hydrate (water/tea), morning routine (e.g., stretch, meditation, skincare). This sets a positive tone for the day.\n*   **7:00 - 8:00 AM:** Exercise/Physical Activity (walk, jog, gym, yoga, etc.) or Prepare a healthy breakfast and eat mindfully.\n*   **8:00 - 9:00 AM:**  Get ready for the day (shower, dress). Review your schedule and to-do list for the day.\n*   **9:00 AM - 12:00 PM:**  Focused Work/Study Block 1.  Tackle your most important tasks when your energy is typically highest.  Use time management techniques (Pomodoro, time blocking).\n*   **12:00 - 1:00 PM:**  Lunch Break. Step away from your work area. Eat a nutritious meal and relax.  Socialize if possible.\n*   **1:00 - 4:00 PM:** Focused Work/Study Block 2. Continue working on your tasks. Schedule meetings or less demanding tasks for this block.\n*   **4:00 - 5:00 PM:**  Admin/Errands/Catch-Up. Answer emails, make phone calls, run errands.\n*   **5:00 - 6:00 PM:**  Free Time / Hobby / Socializing.  Engage in an activity you enjoy or spend time with loved ones.\n*   **6:00 - 7:00 PM:**  Dinner. Prepare or eat a healthy dinner.\n*   **7:00 - 9:00 PM:**  Relaxation / Personal Time.  Read, watch a movie, pursue hobbies, connect with family. Limit screen time closer to bedtime.\n*   **9:00 - 10:00 PM:**  Wind-Down Routine. Prepare for bed (e.g., read, take a bath, gentle stretching).\n*   **10:00 PM:**  Bedtime. Aim for consistent sleep schedule.\n\nI look forward to helping you personalize this!",
